title: Middle school runners finish second, fifth
text:
Middle school runners finish second, fifth By Debbie Holmes 
Trail-Gazette Posted: 10/01/2015 11:52:24 AM MDT Estes Park's Alex Leiga runs during the boys portion of the invite. ( Photos courtesy of Dee Robinson ) 
The Estes Park Middle School cross country teams continue to show their strength. The young Cats competed at the Turner Middle School Invitational on Tuesday, Sept. 29. 
Estes finished second overall for the boys team and fifth overall for the girls. Top finishers include sixth-grader Nolan Marske who finished fifth overall (second in the sixth grade), Paul Robinson was eighth overall (second in seventh grade) and Aiden Gosnell who was eighth overall and third for eighth grade. 
Charly Raymond was the top Estes girl to cross the finish line in second place overall and in her seventh-grade competition, and Samantha Daley finished fifth overall and second for the eighth-grade girls. Seventh-grader Charly Raymond was top finisher for the Ladycats at the Turner Middle School Invite on Tuesday. She placed second overall. ( Photos courtesy of Dee Robinson ) 
The young cross country runners will compete in their league competition in Kersey on Tuesday, Oct. 6 and then those runners who qualify will compete on Oct. 24 in the middle school state meet which will take place at Fehringer Ranch Park in Morrison. Advertisement
